        "refId": "Mitigation Action 9",
        "sector": "Stationary energy: On-site renewable energy generation",
        "description": "Solar Together is a group-buying scheme that delivers cheaper installation of solar panels and battery storage systems for able-to-pay households including home owners and landlords. It is managed by West Sussex County Council, working with agents iChoosr, on behalf of 9 councils in Sussex, including Brighton & Hove City Council. The 3rd round of this scheme closed in March 2024. The 3rd round of the scheme saw a further 64 Solar PV systems and 62 batteries installed in Brighton & Hove. Outcomes across all 3 phases of the scheme (Brighton & Hove only): - 244 installations - 2631 panels installed (970 kWh) - 192 batteries added to PV (1002 kWh) *Note on cost: each local authority contributes to fund a targeted direct mail letter to their residents with the contribution being directly proportionate to the number of residents. That initial investment is recouped by the commission received for each installation, making the initiative cost neutral. The referral fees have paid off the initial mail costs and created a small fund enabling a contribution of approximately \u00a310,000 towards a local cost of living fund. *Note on CO2e estimate: Installed Co2 reduction (year one)",
