        "impacts": "There is already evidence to suggest that previous heatwaves have increased mortality rates of vulnerable people in the city, and that heatwaves are increasing in frequency and severity, and are likely to be worse in the city than surrounding areas due to the urban heat island effect. The greatest impacts are expected to be on those must vulnerable such as children and elderly people and those with existing health conditions. These groups are most likely to suffer from heat-related health conditions, up to and including death. Other potential impacts include disruption within workplaces (particularly those lacking air-conditioning), disruption to education provision from school closures and water scarcity due to increased demand. It should be noted that the main responsibility for this area locally lies with the NHS.",
