        "sector": "Transportation: Other: Net zero actions for the Square Mile - Electric vehicle infrastructure, Zero emissions zone",
        "description": "The City of London Corporation adopted a radical Climate Action Strategy in 2020 which included a target to support the Square Mile to achieve net zero by 2040. A second largest source of emissions in the jurisdiction is from the use of transportation from/to outside the City. Therefore a number of mitigation actions were set out to reduce the Square Mile's transport emissions by 364,000 tCO2e from 2017 to 2040. Mitigation actions include: Electric vehicle infrastructure, Zero emissions zone, timed and permanent street closures.",
