        "sector": "Waste: Implement practices and policies to promote circular economy",
        "description": "Launched in 2025, the City of London Corporation's Circular Economy Framework sets out a vision for the Square Mile to be circular by 2040 - a system where materials never become waste and nature is regenerated. Achieving this requires a major shift in processes, mindsets, and collaboration. The Corporation will first embed circular practices internally, then act as a facilitator for the Square Mile's transition. The framework supports environmental and economic benefits, contributes to net zero goals, and aligns with the Climate Action Strategy. It aims to help existing businesses become more sustainable and create opportunities for new ones, guiding both internal operations and wider City engagement: https://www.cityoflondon.gov.uk/assets/Services-Environment/circular-economy-framework.pdf",
