        "refId": "Mitigation Action 2",
        "sector": "Stationary energy: Building codes and standards",
        "description": "Net Zero New Build / Local Plan Refresh The Net Zero New Build City Challenge was started in 2020, convened by Manchester Climate Change Partnership, led by Civic Engineers, and resulted in the production of a Roadmap for Net Zero Carbon New Buildings in 2021. The Group has recently been reinstated to help integrate net zero new build standards into Manchester's Local Plan which is being updated in 2026. The scope of this ambition includes residential, commercial, industrial, and institutional buildings, plus operational and embodied carbon across the whole life cycle. Output: A set of recommendations to enable net zero new build standards to be readily and successfully incorporated into the Local Plan in Manchester, clarifying how the standards should be applied to different types of development, and phased-in over time in Manchester; with a view to subsequent roll-out across the other nine districts in Greater Manchester.\\n\\nTotal cost of this actions is unknown as is relates to time spent my individual across a large number of organisations.",
