        "sector": "Stationary energy: Other: Climate Change Education / Awareness rasing",
        "description": "Founded and created in Manchester, Carbon Literacy\u00ae provides everyone with access to the vital knowledge, motivation and inspiration they need to start their own low-carbon journey. In practice its unique approach offers a day's worth of experience that delivers awareness, knowledge, motivation and action, resulting in accredited learners, and organisations able to apply and evidence their culture of Carbon Literacy to suppliers, customers and stakeholders. The subject of multiple academic research projects, and an innovation award from the UN, with more than 530 Carbon Literacy solutions are now available globally, created by the learners, communities, organisations and sectors receiving them. As a result, thousands of citizens here in Manchester and tens of thousands of citizens worldwide are now Carbon Literate, acting on climate, changing society and directly reducing emissions globally. \\n\\nOver 9000 citizens in Manchester are now certified as Carbon Literate equating to an estimated 21,600+ tco2e being saved through the actions pledged by participants. \\n\\nGlobally 1078000 citizens certified 215,600+ actions pledge 388,000+ tco2e saved 7,810 organisations engaged across 35 nations, 255 organisations certified as Carbon Literate 782 course designed across 16 sectors Carbon Literacy is \u201cAn awareness of the carbon costs and impacts of everyday activities and the ability and motivation to reduce emissions on an individual community and organisational basis.\u201d http://www.carbonliteracy.com/\\n\\nTotal costs of this action is unknown",
