        "sector": "Stationary energy: Purchase of low-carbon electricity, heat, steam or cooling (i.e., power purchase agreement, supply agreement, renewable energy credit or other sourcing method)",
        "description": "A feasibility study on the potential for large-scale renewable energy generation schemes, including solar PV, onshore or offshore wind, to support the Council's transition to zero carbon began in October 2020. The objective of the study is to identify options to save: 7,000 tonnes of CO2 per year by 2025. The study assesses options to deploy renewables at scale on Council buildings and land, on assets owned by third parties and via different business models. The study recommended a power purchase agreement. Project Team established with external advisors to procure a Power Purchase Agreement (PPA). Clear timeline and resourcing plan established to deliver activities required to have a PPA in place to meet 2025-30 carbon reduction targets. Market engagement session held with developers ahead of the commencement of procurement.https://democracy.manchester.gov.uk/documents/s41111/CCAP%20Quarterly%20Report%20Q1%20v11.pdf",
