        "sector": "Stationary energy: Energy efficiency/ retrofit measures addressing existing commercial, residential and/or municipal buildings",
        "description": "A local partnership group, led by City of York Council, has confirmed an award of \u00a33,371,806 from Innovate UK's Net Zero Living programme. The project will create a Retrofit One-Stop-Shop to facilitate retrofitting homes with low-carbon measures, improve the householder experience and contribute to better energy efficiency standards across the city. The project, which aims to eliminate barriers to retrofitting properties with carbon reduction measures, will involve engagement with residents, creating 'deep retrofit' demonstrator homes, developing supply chain skills and ways to match approved suppliers and products to needs, and exploring innovative financing methods. As the number of houses that will utilise the one-stop-shop is currently unknown, it is not possible to know the carbon and energy savings that will be achieved at this stage. The modelling work undertaken within this project has indicated that this approach could achieve a 31% to 49% reduction in CO2e emissions within our focus area, based on an assumed uptake of between 20% to 50%. https://www.york.gov.uk/climate-change-2/BuiltEnvironment/4#:~:text=Retrofit%20One%2DStop%2DShop%20York,-A%20local%20partnership&text=The%20project%20will%20create%20a,efficiency%20standards%20across%20the%20city.",
