        "description": "Continuous delivery of a behaviour change\\nprogramme on cycling and walking to\\nencourage non-car modes as the best choice for short joruneys - Climate Change Action Plan. https://democracy.york.gov.uk/%28S%28iezd4m45k3tmf22josjfte55%29%29/documents/s179441/Annex%20A_York%20Climate%20Change%20Action%20Plan_2024.pdf \\n\\nThe cost of full scale behaviour change programme funded by national government schemes illustrated for the costs. One of York's largest behaviour change levers currently is the active travel app BetterPoints, which forms art of a wider approach to awareness and education of non-motorized transport. The Council has adopted Better Points as platform to increase sustainable journeys across the city. There are over 4,250 downloads from York of the BetterPoints app and sustainable joruneys are monitored as well as how often these journeys have replaced cars. This programme has reduced emissions by an estimated 1,298tCO2e. 158tco2e is the current estimated annual emissions reduction. In one year More than 610,000 active and bus journeys were recorded and 346,000 active and bus journeys have directly replaced single occupancy car trips according to user surveys. \\n",
