        "impacts": "Temperatures are certain to continue to rise, perhaps reaching a worst-case further increase by the end of the century of 5\u00baC or more under unchecked emissions. Although probably more in the range of 1\u00baC to 2\u00baC under the Paris Agreement. \\n\\nHeat waves and associated heat risks including fire are likely to increase over Cornwall through the century, potentially reaching levels currently associated with areas of Central and Southern Europe towards the end of the century. \\n\\nExtreme heat is an acute health hazard for those over 65, people with existing health conditions and populations in urban environments. Projected increase in the frequency of heatwaves will have a range of impacts on homes, communities and critical infrastructure. New houses which have very high levels of energy efficiency can be susceptible to overheating by 'keeping the heat in'. \\n\\nMeanwhile, houses which are poorly insulated are very hard to heat, causing cold and damp conditions.\\n\\n\u2022Increasing summer temperatures, in addition to increased heat waves, may impact the health of livestock. People who work in outdoor industries are more susceptible to the effects of extreme heat. \\n\\n\u2022Increases in extreme weather events, including drought, heat waves, and intense rainfall, may increase forest damage. Increases in mean air temperature, increased frequency of heatwaves will have a range of impacts on businesses. Including heat exhaustion and heat stroke, in addition to risks to stock and inventory, as well as supply chain disruption. \\n\\nThe elderly, young people and people with chronic health conditions are more likely to experience heat stress and heatstroke.\\n\\nLow income households or those in poverty are less likely to be able to afford or have access to air conditioning or cooling devices, which make them more vulnerable to heat. \\n\\nInfrastructure such as power grids and water supplies are susceptible to extreme heat and ecosystems can be disrupted due to stress and death in wildlife.",
