        "impacts": "Coastal erosion presents significant risks to local communities by gradually wearing away shorelines, leading to the loss of land, homes, and infrastructure. This process can undermine roads, utilities, and buildings, posing safety hazards and increasing vulnerability to flooding. Economically, it can disrupt tourism, agriculture, and fisheries, which many coastal areas rely on. Environmentally, erosion threatens habitats such as dunes and wetlands, reducing biodiversity and weakening natural coastal defences. Additionally, cultural heritage sites and historically significant landmarks may be irreversibly damaged or lost, impacting community identity and history.\\n\\nCoastal vulnerability mapping: https://experience.arcgis.com/experience/a3074c31108a43ada55e21e660bc043d/",
