        "impacts": "Coventry is particularly vulnerable to surface water flooding during heavy rainfall events. During winter of 2019, Coventry experienced higher than average rainfall rates, causing significant surface water flooding similar localised incidents have occurred . The surface water mostly impacted public transport and road traffic. In October 2021, there was a flood warning in Coventry, with water entering shops and businesses, and impeding everyday life. It is likely the intensity and frequency of rainfall and consequently surface water flooding will increase in the future which could affect industry and the economy if it prevents the public getting to and from work safely. In October 2023, Coventry was issued with flood warning alert from the Environment Agency during storm Babet and again in 2024. The Environment Agency in early 2025 after the production of the ARP4 Report in Dec 2024 confirmed a projection for an increased risk of flooding both Fluvial and Pluvial especially the latter.",
