        "description": "The Dundee Local Heat and Energy Efficiency Strategy (LHEES) has identified the scale of the opportunity for heat networks to decarbonise heat in the city's buildings, with five prioritised heat network zones identified of strategic importance. Working towards delivering on the Local Heat and Energy Efficiency Delivery Plan, the Council has started preparations to secure specialist legal advice to undertake a detailed appraisal of options and provide a recommendation, based on sound evidence, of the most appropriate heat network delivery model to be adopted to unlock heat network deployment within the city. This includes a comprehensive assessment of the risks and challenges and a recommended procurement strategy, centred on the City Centre Heat Network zone as the initial project, with acknowledgment for expansion to the further four prioritised heat network zones.\\n\\nhttps://www.dundeecity.gov.uk/reports/agendas/fwegi%20230924(pub).pdf (page 22)",
