        "description": "Using greenspace and Low & Zero Carbon Technologies to decarbonise sports centres. The scheme has been developed in such a way that the size of each technology has been optimised to achieve the best carbon emissions reductions at the lowest practical fuel costs. In line with the Scottish Government's Renewable Energy Targets, the Energy Hub will be capable of generating 100% of its electrical demand and provide 85% of the site's heat demand from renewables. It is estimated that the project has the potential to save 22% CO2 emissions based on a typical gas fired boiler plant, which equates to 536 tonnes per annum or over 13,400 tonnes of CO2 over its life.",
