        "sector": "Stationary energy: Energy efficiency/ retrofit measures addressing existing commercial, residential and/or municipal buildings",
        "description": "Installing External Wall Insulation (EWI) on hard to treat buildings to improve energy efficiency. Dundee City Council's Housing Department is monitoring energy use and energy bill saving before and after EWI insulation to make sure that the Council's project is making positive impact. Currently the Council's EWI projects are being re-designed to comply with the new PAS:2035 retrofit standard which include designing out cold-bridging and the requirement for the appointment of a suitably qualified Retrofit Co-ordinator, to ensure the production of long-term energy efficiency retrofit plans for every property. Total investments of more than \u00a350 million since 2013 with more than 5,000 residents in Dundee seeing their properties thermally upgraded. For more information about the project, follow the link here: \\n\\nhttps://sustainabledundee.co.uk/case-studies/dundee-ewi",
