        "refId": "Mitigation Action 12",
        "sector": "Transportation: Improve walking, cycling and integrated transit access",
        "description": "Bell Street Green Transport Hub - Reimagining the Bell Street Mulit-Storey Car Park: Green transport hub and spokes project - in 2023, Dundee City Council secured Levelling Up funding to redevelop the Bell Street multi-storey car park into a multi-modal, sustainable transport hub. The green transport mobility hub aims to become a destination for the city by:\\n\u2022\\tEnhancing access and connectivity to key amenities such as employment, education, health, and leisure facilities in the city through enhanced walking and cycling links to the city centre\\n\u2022\\tDecreasing carbon emissions by promoting a shift towards low-carbon modes of transportation and encouraging the transition from private car usage to active travel options\\n\u2022\\tAlleviating congestion and improving air quality by increasing the availability of electric vehicle (EV) charge points thereby encouraging the use of zero tailpipe emission vehicles, while also minimising motorised vehicle deliveries in the city centre to enhance convenience for businesses\\n\\nThe new facility will include approximately 350 EV charge points, feature a significant solar array and battery storage system, and serve as a cycle hub with indoor cycle training space and pumptrack for bicycles, BMX, scooters and adaptive bikes in a first of its kind facility for Scotland.\\n\\nThe Bell Street Green Transport Hub is due to open in autumn this year (2025) with the new facility opening on the ground floor next spring (2026). The project is known to incorporate the principles of circular economy in its design as well as in the management of materials and other resources for repurpose. \\n\\nMore information on the project can be found here: https://www.dundeecity.gov.uk/news/article?article_ref=4936\\n",
