        "renewableTarget": "This plan is based on climate-related scenarios and impacts described in the Essex Climate Action Commission (ECAC)'s report 'Net Zero: Making Essex Carbon Neutral'. (https://www.essexclimate.org.uk/sites/default/files/DS21_7178%20ECAC_Commission_Report-Final.pdf). The ECAC commissioned a study to investigate the impact of its recommendations for climate actions, including a baseline of emissions in Essex and a future emissions pathway, resulting in the report 'Essex Baseline and Pathway to Net Zero' published in 2021. (https://www.essex.gov.uk/sites/default/files/migration_data/files/assets.ctfassets.net/knkzaf64jx5x/rzuw1LpExzIc9v4dUjk03/dcb7427bf2569c3a75134addc2d27dd2/Climate-Action-Baseline-and-Pathway-to-Net-Zero.pdf ). This report is supplemented by the work performed for Essex County Council by Element Energy in 2020 in producing the study \u201cEssex Future Energy Scenarios and Pathways to Net Zero (Phase 1)\u201d. ECC's climate action plans have been developed based on High Emission Scenario, assuming continued increases in greenhouse gas emissions under a high RCP8.5 emissions or \u201cbusiness as usual\u201d scenario. Essex can expect a continued upward trend in temperatures, as well as generally hotter summers and warmer winters. The projected rainfall data informs drier summers and wetter winters.\\n",
