        "sector": "Stationary energy: Energy efficiency/ retrofit measures addressing existing commercial, residential and/or municipal buildings",
        "description": "Housing Services are drafting a Housing Retrofit Position Statement for presentation at November 2025 Net Zero Committee. This highlights the current low rate of home retrofit in the city stemming primarily from an absence of statutory regulation and affordability issues. It identifies actions to steadily increase the energy efficiency and decarbonisation of Glasgow's homes. This includes five early actions: maximising existing grants; heat pump accelerator; pre-1919 tenement energy efficiency improvements; improving existing heating system efficiency, and public awareness raising. And six supporting actions: funding and finance; supply chain & skills development; retrofit information advice and support services; digital platforms, policy & communication and building energy performance modelling and monitoring.",
