        "sector": "Stationary energy: Energy efficiency/ retrofit measures addressing existing commercial, residential and/or municipal buildings",
        "description": "The Mayor's Retrofit Accelerator - Workplaces (RA-W) programme (formerly RE:FIT London) has already supported the retrofit of over 1200 public sector buildings in London since 2009, to date saving almost 58,000 tonnes of CO2 per annum and millions of pounds from public sector energy bills. Jointly funded with ERDF, the Accelerator helps a range of organisations including London boroughs, NHS bodies, central government departments, schools and other educational establishments, and cultural and heritage organisations to implement retrofit projects that reduce energy use and/or decarbonise energy supply (such as heating systems).Since 2020 the Mayor's Retrofit Accelerator - Workplaces has also been successful in helping London's public sector secure funding to install energy measures. The programme has supported organisations to develop projects that have successfully received over \u00a3330 million through the government's Public Sector Decarbonisation Scheme. Projects include energy efficiency and decarbonisation of heating systems in schools, academies, healthcare, local government buildings. The programme closed in spring 2024, to be succeeded by the Mayor's Zero Carbon Accelerator.",
