        "sector": "Stationary energy: Other: Cross-cutting: retrofit, energy systems, air quality, adaptation, zero waste, circular economy",
        "description": "Future Neighbourhoods 2030 is \u00a37.7 million programme which aims to tackle some of London's defining environmental challenges, including the climate emergency and toxic air quality, whilst creating jobs, developing skills and supporting a just transition to a low carbon circular economy. There are 12 Future Neighbourhoods, which are in some of London's disadvantaged and climate vulnerable areas, or where residents are likely to have been severely impacted by the pandemic. Somers Town in Camden, and Notting Dale in Kensington and Chelsea, have received funding to develop strategies and work with residents to deliver a wide range of innovative and pioneering projects. These projects have been developed with the local community and will bring the benefits of transitioning to net zero to residents. The 10 other Future Neighbourhoods received funding to develop visionary strategies and plans to reach net zero by 2030. These strategies have been created with local communities and provide a clear pathway to a net zero future for neighbourhoods across London.",
