        "hazard": "Mass movement",
        "vulnerableGroups": "Outdoor workers|Frontline workers",
        "sectorsExposed": "Transportation and storage|Conservation|Water supply|Forestry|Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply|Financial and insurance activities|Real estate activities|Information and communication|Human health and social work activities",
        "impacts": "Vulnerable population: Outdoor workers would experience direct exposure to mass movement events, creating a dangerous work environment, where work may need to be postponed. Frontline workers would have to manage an increase in demand for services, or may be unable to access patients due to road closures.Sectors: Forestry can be negatively affected as mass movement would damage tree and plant stock. Conservation may be impacted if peatlands or protected areas are damaged from mass movement. Energy supply can be impacted through damage to energy assets and other infrastructure and power cuts can arise from damage to powerlines - this also impacts information and communication systems. Transport may be disrupted due to road closure from debris and an increase in accidents may occur. Mass movement damaging businesses, real estate, infrastructure and such would lead to insurance claims and negatively impact financial activities. Mass movement poses a risk to the homeless community, could damage council housing, and increases risk of injuries, alongside causing delivery issues, and disrupting health and social care delivery.",
        "populationExposed": "91-100%",
