        "sector": "Transportation: Improve fuel economy and reduce CO2 emissions from motorized vehicles",
        "description": "Clean Air Zone (CAZ)A Clean Air Zone (CAZ) is now in place for parts of Newcastle and Gateshead to help improve air quality and reduce the number of high polluting vehicles using our roads. In January 2023, if you drive an older taxi, van, bus, coach or heavy goods vehicle (HGV) you may have to pay a CAZ charge. Charges for non-compliant vans and LGVs started in July 2023. Our 2024 Air Quality Status report shows how air pollution appears to have fallen across much of the city in the first year of the CAZ tolls. There has been a drop in the average level of nitrogen dioxide (NO2) at all but one of the 70 monitoring stations in Newcastle.",
