        "sector": "Transportation: Procurement of electric vehicles for government fleet",
        "description": "In January 2023 we launched our Green Fleet Procurement Policy which mandates the procurement of ULEVs to replace an existing combustion vehicle within the NCC fleet (excludes certain speciality vehicles and HGV's). The policy also looks holistically at efficiency gain within the fleet, the infrastructure and logistical requirements from fleet replacements, and the use of interim arrangements for vehicles that can not viably transition currently. Since the launch of the policy 13.7% of our fleet is now electric. The vehicles are being assessed on a case by case basis for vehicle replacement and will be continuing until full fleet decarbonisation is achieved.",
