        "description": "North Tyneside Council is spending over \u00a34.3m is being spent to convert almost 20,000 street lights to energy efficient LED lights. Approximately 97% of street lights have been converted to LED, with fewer than 1,000 units remaining. This is likely to reduce electricity consumption by over 50%. As well as generating energy savings of 1,000 tonnes of carbon each year, the 20,000 new LED streetlights will also save the council around \u00a31m in electricity costs. https://my.northtyneside.gov.uk/news/30439/council-flicks-switch-final-phase-street-lighting-project",
