        "sector": "Transportation: Improve walking, cycling and integrated transit access",
        "description": "The Northumberland Local Cycling and Walking Infrastructure Plan (LCWIP) was approved in April 2025. The LCWIP sets out plans to improve cycling and walking infrastructure throughout the county, with focus on 12 main towns. Through the LCWIP development process, 65 priority cycling and walking corridors were identified. 7 schemes are currently in delivery, and 9 further schemes are in the design and development stage. \\nhttps://northumberland.moderngov.co.uk/documents/s25394/Northumberland+Local+Cycling+and+Walking+Infrastructure+Plans.pdf\\nhttps://www.northumberland.gov.uk/NorthumberlandCountyCouncil/media/News/2024/March/Square/Climate-Change-Action-Plan-2024-26.pdf\\n",
