        "refId": "Mitigation Action 5",
        "sector": "Stationary energy: Domestic and/or commercial heat network",
        "description": "Since 2020, NCC have been developing proposals for district heating networks in 8 of the largest settlements in Northumberland that have substantial heat customers such as leisure centres. Heat masterplanning studies have been completed for 6 towns and Techno-Economic feasibility studies have been completed for 2 towns. Legal and commercial advisors have been appointed to assist in developing a procurement approach that seeks to use Local Authority heat loads (primarily leisure centres) as 'anchor customers' to stimulate private sector investment in heat networks where they are commercially viable and value for money. If fully realised, the heat networks are estimated to have the potential to reduce building heating CO2 emissions by 35,630 tonnes annually.",
        "status": "2020",
