        "impacts": "Health Risks\\nSmoke inhalation from wildfires can worsen respiratory conditions like asthma especially among older adults and children.\\nPeatland fires are particularly hazardous, releasing fine particulate matter and carbon monoxide, which can linger for days.\\n\\nEmergency services under pressure: long-duration fires that smoulder underground in peat pose a challenge. There will be increased demand for rapid response and coordination with park rangers and local authorities.\\n-Vulnerable populations\\nElderly residents, people with disabilities, and those with chronic illnesses are at higher risk during wildfire events.\\nLimited mobility and access to transport can hinder evacuation.\\n\\nFarmers face loss of grazing land, fencing, and livestock during wildfires.\\n",
