        "impacts": "Heavy precipitation occurring on a more frequent basis poses a challenge for sewerage systems and water management. This can result in flooding of homes and businesses, and flooding of roads presenting challenges to transportation and distribution of goods.\\nVulnerable populations such as elderly persons may be less willing or able to leave their homes, or may be at heightened risk of slips and falls, increasing pressures on health and social care providers.\\nExcessive rainfall may adversely impact on agricultural productivity in the wider county of Norfolk.\\nConstruction sites may be inundated with rainfall such that activities need to halt, extending the length of time required to complete projects and having knock-on economic impacts.\\nFlooding of low-lying properties may also adversely impact on real estate activities if prospective purchasers view this is as a reason not to proceed with the purchase of a property due to concerns of increasing their personal vulnerability to the impacts of climate change.",
