        "description": "Nottingham's Carbon Neutral Action Plan includes a range of actions to reduce emissions associated with freight transport in the city. This includes actions around the key objectives to: - have a clean system for freight to enter and move around the city, by reducing the impact of freight moving around the city. \\n\\nFurther details on specific actions for each objective are included at: https://www.nottinghamcity.gov.uk/media/2619917/2028-carbon-neutral-action-plan-v2-160620.pdf Nottingham's annual reviews of the action plan are published at: https://www.nottinghamcity.gov.uk/your-council/about-the-council/carbon-neutral-nottingham-2028/why-do-we-need-to-act/ The total estimated annual emissions reductions captures if all these actions were delivered, and currently known/anticipated local and national policy is delivered. \\n\\nThe estimate also includes interdependencies with other actions, estimated in the same way, for example related to grid decarbonisation. Some of these actions are reliant on funding that is not yet secured or significant Government action in all areas, including planning, legislation, policy and regulation.",
