        "sectorsExposed": "Accommodation and food service activities|Real estate activities|Construction",
        "impacts": "Ever changing weather conditions associated with climate change are likely to impact buildings and infrastructure in Oxford. For example, it is expected that the UK will see heavier rainfall events occurring more frequently (particularly in Winter), which raises the flood risk and associated damage to buildings and infrastructure. Additionally, rising temperatures are likely to disturb the historic building stock in Oxford, since increased heat and humidity can accelerate the chemical processes which cause the building materials to deteriorate. Furthermore, it's likely that storms and strong winds will increase in frequency and intensity over the coming years. This will increase the likelihood of fallen trees or flying debris causing damage to infrastructure and buildings.",
