        "vulnerableGroups": "Other: Social housing occupants|Children and youth|Elderly",
        "sectorsExposed": "Human health and social work activities|Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply|Construction",
        "impacts": "There is an evident higher current heatwave hazard in urban areas such as Oxford City due to greater urban and suburban areas, higher cooling degree days and lower proportion of green space. Key railway stations and routes are located in Oxford City which have a high heatwave hazard.Summertime overheating in both new and existing dwellings is widespread and increasing, even in temperate climates. Many buildings in Oxford are designed to retain heat, therefore periods of extreme heat bring increased risks of overheating for the building occupants. High temperatures in homes negatively impact people's lives. Sleep is disrupted, with knock on impacts on health and productivity. Even more seriously, overheating effects mortality and morbitity, with elderly and vulnerable populations particularly affected.",
