        "impacts": "Overall, wind speed is expected to increase slightly in the winter and decrease slightly in the summer so the risks posed by high winds may be lower due to climate change. However, the likelihood of storms and gusts is uncertain.\\n\\nStorm (wind) events have caused significant damage in Perth & Kinross over the last five years, with some rural communities losing electricity for over a week, as well as risks to transport, nature, forestry and physical damage",
        "populationExposed": "41-50%",
