        "impacts": "See also text above on river flooding much of which applies to urban (surface water) flooding. A Preliminary Flood Risk Assessment was completed for Reading in 2011, 2 years after the Flood Risk Regulations 2009 placed a duty on the Council to prepare such an assessment by June 2011. This estimated some 7,600 properties were at risk of flooding to a depth greater than 0.3m during a 1 in 200 annual chance rainfall event, out of a total of c. 65,410 households - giving the figure cited of between 10-20% of the population being exposed to the risk of flooding. Vulnerable groups will be inherently more exposed to flood risk in view of factors such as reduced mobility, availability of resources to adapt etc.",
