        "refId": "Mitigation Action 1",
        "sector": "Transportation: Procurement of zero emissions buses",
        "description": "32 zero emission full EV buses will become operational in Reading in autumn 2025 following successful trials in June 2024 and a successful funding bids which secured a total of \u00a36m in Government funding to enable the transition. Reading Buses, which is owned by the local authority, already has one of the most environmentally friendly bus fleets in the country (see mitigation action 3) but the funding, from the Department of Transport's Zero Emissions Bus Regional Area (ZEBRA) 2 scheme, provides for 75% of the difference in the cost of a zero emission vehicle compared to the diesel equivalent, and 75% of the cost of installing 13 fast chargers. The remainder of the cost will be met by Reading Buses. The vehicles incorporate heat pumps to provide air conditioning in summer and heating in winter. https://www.reading.gov.uk/news/eight-new-electric-buses-for-reading/tonnes for fleet of c.87 diesel buses - 32 of these (37% of the diesel fleet) will be replaced by zero-emission vehicles in 2025 - 36.7% reduction in diesel emissions = 6254 tonnes estimated carbon saving.",
