        "description": "In March 2022 the Council committed a further \u00a3976,000 to an existing \u00a340m million project for new leisure facilities at Rivermead and Palmer Park to enable additional carbon reduction measures. The Council and it's partners GLL, who operate the leisure centres, had already committed to build the new facilities to BREEAM 'Excellent' standards, including \u00a31.6 million of energy saving measures, but the additional measures are further enhancing the environmental performance of the buildings. The additional investment was estimated to reduce the emissions from the buildings by 57% and 80% respectively. The new Palmer Park leisure centre opened in December 2022 and the new Rivermead leisure centre opened in July 2023. Details are available at: https://democracy.reading.gov.uk/ieDecisionDetails.aspx?ID=688. A case study was written up for the Local Government Association and can be viewed at https://www.local.gov.uk/case-studies/readings-low-carbon-leisure-programme. Additionally in 2025, the council finished installing heat pumps into its civic offices utilising renewable heat sources. In 2024 the Council drilled two 120m boreholes into the aquifer to access the latent heat available underground to heat its theatre. The solar programme continued in 2024 with procurement started on a solar canopies project at the Councils depot site and surveys and feasibility work on a solar farm to power the Smallmead materials recycling facility. These will add to the 2MW of solar the council has already installed on housing, council and community buildings since 2011.",
