        "sector": "Other, please specify: Other: Formal training for the senior management of the jurisdiction",
        "description": "In 2023 the Council initiated a formal Carbon Literacy training programme for senior leaders in the organisation, in partnership with a national body, the Carbon Literacy Project, which develops and licenses training materials for this purpose. Between September 2023 and June 2025 80 senior officers and 6 elected members, including the Leader and Deputy Leader of the Council, were certified 'carbon literate'; having completed the training and met the required standard in an external assessment conducted by the Carbon Literacy Project. In February 2024 Reading Borough Council achieved 'Carbon Literate Organisation (Bronze) status having met the required standards set by the Carbon Literacy Project. The programme continues to deliver and during 2024 a further 31 people having been trained, bringing the total to 99 people trained (12 have left organisation).",
