        "refId": "Mitigation Action 26",
        "sector": "Stationary energy: On-site renewable energy generation",
        "description": "Reading Borough Council joined with other Berkshire Councils to launch the Berkshire Solar Together scheme in 2023. The scheme offers solar and battery installations to residents, using collective buying power to negotiate competitive prices. The first round saw 0.64MW of solar capacity installed via 1,568 panels in 148 installations, with an estimated 25 yr CO2 reduction of 3,131,865kg and a total investment value of \u00a31,348,504. It also led to 0.84mWh of battery capacity in 125 installations. The Council is participating in a second round of the scheme in 2024",
