        "description": "The Council secured \u00a3850k to take a private sector concession (estimated at \u00a315m) to install 1500 electric vehicle charging points across the town. The charging points will be installed on street locations where residents do not have access to off-street private parking. The project is being run in conjunction with a programme to install 'gulleys' in the street to allow private home owners to connect their electric vehicles to their own charging facilities where they do not have private off-street parking available to them. Emission reduction assume that the infrastructure will allow 1500 additional EVs and would displace 90% of their emissions for an average of 9000 miles per annum.",
