        "sector": "Waste: Increase awareness/engage public on waste reduction/recycling measures",
        "description": "Promote carbon-efficient behaviours among residents, visitors, businesses, and other organisations to decrease carbon emissions associated with waste. By encouraging responsible waste management practices, significant reductions in carbon footprints can be achieved across the community.\\n\\nThese include rolling out a Waste Hierarchy Framework to prioritise waste avoidance and reduction, promoting carbon-efficient behaviours across communities, and eliminating food waste through sustainable consumption practices. Additional efforts aim to improve recycling efficiency, reduce contamination in kerbside collections, and collaborate with food businesses to cut food waste by 50% by 2030.",
