        "vulnerableGroups": "Low-income households|Marginalized/minority communities|Vulnerable health groups|Women and girls|Elderly|Children and youth|Other: Generally most of the Borough|Outdoor workers",
        "sectorsExposed": "Manufacturing|Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply|Accommodation and food service activities|Sewerage, waste management and remediation activities|Water supply|Forestry|Construction|Human health and social work activities|Conservation|Agriculture",
        "impacts": "Water quality in West Midlands aquifers is generally poor, and much of the water used for consumption comes from other areas surrounding the Borough. Increased demand during heatwaves and other events is likely to put strain on water infrastructure, meaning an increase in hosepipe bans and other water restriction measures.",
