        "sector": "Stationary energy: Increase use of clean energy sources for heating and cooling buildings",
        "description": "The Council has started a programme of installing heat pumps in its corporate buildings. The main Council House project is now completed, and the programme is being continued in a major leisure centre in Sandwell (Tipton Leisure Centre) across 2024-25, replacing the gas powered boilers with Air-water heat pumps. The new project is expected to save 240 tonnes of CO2 per year. As part of the new Devolved Funding Deal, the Council hopes to further this programme in 2026 with a further 20 sites that together should reduce annual emissions by 340 tonnes CO2e per year.",
