        "refId": "Mitigation Action 21",
        "sector": "Industrial Processes and Product: Action to decarbonize building/construction materials",
        "description": "SCC's Highways team have replaced traditional resurfacing of carriageway surface course with a cold applied surface rejuvenator. This was a 'pilot' scheme but Sunderland Council are thought to be the 1st in the north-east region to use this product. This will save energy, carbon and be less costly. \\nSunderland Council are now monitoring the condition of the road surface over the next 2 years to see if any deterioration. The Council may use the surface again during 2026 at a suitable site. \\n \\nhttps://www.sunderland.gov.uk/article/14887/Roads-and-bridges\\n\\n",
