        "renewableTarget": "This plan sets out activities that are to be undertaken by the Climate Change team, some of which are in association with local residents, NGOs and national government, to increase biodiversity in Warwick District and to do events/activities that raise awareness about the importance of biodiversity e.g. No Mow May. It sets out the specific kinds of area that will be particularly targeted (wood pasture and parkland, trees, woodland, grassland, main rivers and canals, native hedgerows, arable field margins and wetlands and ponds), as well as twenty target species, including the bat, the slow worm, the hedgehog and the barn owl. It also explains how progress will be monitored and reported and gives a list of Objectives to be met, with a suggested end date.",
