        "impacts": "Within Wokingham Borough, relatively few vulnerable sites are located within flood risk areas (this includes hospitals and schools). Of these most are within Flood Zone 2, which is acceptable for all the vulnerability classifications in these instances (more vulnerable, less vulnerable and essential infrastructure). However, emergency plans should be put in place for the event of an extreme flood. Maps show that many of the key population centres within the Borough are situated adjacent to river corridors, resulting in a number of properties being at risk of fluvial flooding and in areas of significant surface water flood risk. However, the percentage of properties shown to be at risk makes up a small proportion of the total number of properties within the Borough. The primary impacts reside around housing and businesses in at risk areas, with the latter at risk of being unable to operate until some time after flooding events. Low income households are only the most affected in this current scenario in terms of being less able to recover quickly from the effects of any event. The risk of any event reaching/ impacting on low income households is very similar to that of non low income properties.",
